                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="35248" author="balex" created="Wed, 30 Apr 2008 19:08:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am hesitant to remove constructor argument validation on account of what is a remoting protocol consideration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have you tired registering a custom Serializer/Deserializer that can handle GrantedAuthorityImpl with com.caucho.hessian.io.SerializerFactory? Spring&apos;s HessianClientInterceptor and HessianServiceExporter classes both offer a setSerializerFactory(SerializerFactory) to make it easy to plug in these sort of customizations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="36171" author="luke" created="Tue, 27 May 2008 21:41:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No response so I&apos;m closing the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="37368" author="fritzrichter" created="Sun, 6 Jul 2008 11:10:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Ben Alex,&lt;br/&gt;
cause I&apos;ve got the same problem, I want to ask you, if you can provide an example for your solution.&lt;br/&gt;
The problem is, that the object (GrantedAuthority) has no DefaultConstuctor. So why can&apos;t it be a solution, to add such a constructor and a getter/setter as well?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this can&apos;t be a solution, it would be great, if you can give me a hint, how to write such a serializer/deserializer for this object.&lt;br/&gt;
Kind regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Fritz &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="37409" author="balex" created="Tue, 8 Jul 2008 03:12:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did take a look at Hessian&apos;s support for custom serializers/deserializers at the time of the original comment. The Hessian documentation/samples shows code which uses complex constructors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is really more of a Hessian-specific question, so I&apos;d encourage you to avail yourself of Hessian support options/forums etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d also suggest perhaps considering using a remoting protocol based on Java serialization, such as Spring&apos;s HttpInvoker or RMI, as both will work with the present GrantedAuthorityImpl.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="126789" author="issuemaster" created="Sat, 6 Feb 2016 06:36:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/1038&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/1038&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
